ANC's Jackson Mthembu at the ANC National Conference in Nasrec Expo on 5 July 2017. JOHANNESBURG - The minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu has tested positive for COVID-19. READ: Ramaphosa, NCCC to meet stakeholders over COVID-19 spike The Presidency confirmed the minister tested positive after presenting with symptoms on Monday. People who have been in contact with the minister are self-quarantining. "He remains in high spirits and wishes all those who are also fighting the coronavirus a speedy recovery," a statement issued by the Presidency read. Mthembu urged South Africans regularly wash their hands, wear masks and practice social distancing. Minister Mthembu tests positive for Covid-19 https://t.co/9AmWBDsBqD